nd Mycoplasma</italic> above</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">See above</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;<italic>Mycoplasma pneumoniae</italic></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">See above under Acute bronchitis</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">See <italic>Chlamydia</italic> and <italic>Mycoplasma</italic> above</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">See above</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;<italic>Streptococcus pneumoniae</italic></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Gram stain<break/>Aerobic bacterial culture</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"/></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Urine antigen<sup>f</sup></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">First voided clean-catch urine specimen</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Sterile container, RT, 2 h</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;<italic>Pseudomonas aeruginosa</italic></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Gram stain<break/>Aerobic bacterial culture</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Expectorated sputum</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Sterile container, RT, 2 h or &#x0003e;2&#x02013;24 h, 2&#x000b0;C&#x02013;8&#x000ba;C</td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" rowspan="1"> &#x02003;Viruses</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2" colspan="1">&#x02003;&#x02003;Rhinovirus<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;Coronavirus<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;PIV (most often PIV3)<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;Influenza virus<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;RSV<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;HMPV<break/>&#x02003;&#x02003;Adenoviruses</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Rapid antigen detection tests<sup>b</sup><break/>Virus culture<sup>c</sup></td><td rowspan="2" colspan="1">Nasal aspirates or washes, NP swabs or aspirates, throat washes or swabs</td><td rowspan="2" colspan="1">VTM or sterile container (washes, etc, transport RT &#x0003c;2 h or refrigerated (2&#x000b0;C&#x02013;8&#x000b0;C), 24&#x02013;48 h</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">NAAT<sup>d</sup></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" rowspan="1">
